Description: Ibanez S570B WH Item Description S570B is a solid body model introduced in 2010 for the Ibanez S series. The same series S470B was replaced with a 24 fret neck and a new inlay, which used to be 22 frets for all S models before, but in 2008 released the first 24 frets S Prestige model based on S5470, All S models in 2010 became 24 frets. The S570B attached a black binding to the body of the mahogany, bolted to the maple neck, and a white wave shape position marker on the 24 fret rosewood fingerboard. Components include an Ibanez Infinity pickup, a pickup ring adjacent to a single coil is fitted with a pair of humbuckers and a ZR double lock tremolo bridge with a removable ZPS tuning stabilizer is installed. 【SPEC】 Body : Mahogany Neck : Maple Fingerboard : Rosewood Pickups : HSH Weight : 3.5kg Color : White Serial Number : Condition: Used · Each metal part has dullness. String height: Adjusted on 14 frets with 1 string 1.5 mm to 6 string 2.0 mm. All Electronics/Hardware function as they should.
